OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1784134075
OL,3,CWhen will the rain return? UK heatwave
OL,4,Cand dry spell set to continue
OL,6,FThis year has already beaten the
OL,7,Frecord for the most days above 34C,
OL,8,Fand there have been as many 30C days
OL,9,Fin 2026 as in the infamous year of
OL,10,F1976, the Met Office said.
OL,12,FFarmers and gardeners are likely
OL,13,Fdesperate for rain as many areas have
OL,14,Fbeen dry for more than a week.
OL,16,FThere have been 19 wildfires across
OL,17,Fthe UK, and a yellow heat alert is
OL,18,Fstill in effect until Friday.
OL,20,FWhen will it rain?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1784134075
OL,3,CWhen will the rain return? UK heatwave
OL,4,Cand dry spell set to continue
OL,6,FTemperatures are not set to cool down
OL,7,Fin the immediate future, according to
OL,8,Fthe Met Office. With high-pressure
OL,9,Fdominating weather systems, the
OL,10,Fprolonged heat is set to continue,
OL,11,Fadding to the already dry conditions.
OL,13,FOnly some local areas have seen
OL,14,Fshowers and thunderstorms this week,
OL,15,Fand for the next few days most of the
OL,16,FUK will be rain-free.
OL,18,FThe weather forecaster said there is a
OL,19,Fchance of scattered showers in the far
OL,20,Fsouth or southwest on Thursday
OL,21,Fafternoon, but this won't last long.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1784134075
OL,3,CWhen will the rain return? UK heatwave
OL,4,Cand dry spell set to continue
OL,6,FThunderstorms could also occur in
OL,7,Flocal areas, with brief periods of
OL,8,Frainfall, but the chances are low, and
OL,9,Fit won't have a nationwide impact.
OL,11,FHow unusual is this?
OL,13,FJuly is no stranger to heat. In 2022,
OL,14,FConingsby in Lincolnshire recorded a
OL,15,Fwhopping 40.3C.
OL,17,FThe current heatwave has already
OL,18,Fsurpassed last year's July temperature
OL,19,Frecord of 35.8C, recording 36C in many
OL,20,Fcounties in the south and southeast of
OL,21,FEngland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
